               <head>Homiliary; English, late 12th cent.</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_d_35-item1">
                     <locus>(fol.1–30v)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14583">Sermons</title>
                     <note>By <persName key="person_15161579" role="aut"> Guillelmus de Merula </persName> (nos. 2–19 in Schneyer, <title>Rep</title>. II, pp.494–6) with others interspersed.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_d_35-item2">
                     <locus>(fol.32–224)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14583">Sermons</title>
                     <note>A large collection of sermons arranged roughly according to the church year, including sermons by <persName key="person_59875293" role="aut"> Bernard of Clairvaux </persName>, <persName key="person_84971682" role="aut"> Ivo of Chartres </persName>, <persName key="person_54538580" role="aut"> Geoffrey Babion </persName>, <persName key="person_282035032" role="aut"> Hildebert of Lavardin </persName>, <persName key="person_15161243" role="aut"> Gébouin of Troyes </persName>, <persName key="person_40175167" role="aut"> Petrus Comestor </persName>, <persName key="person_9865788" role="aut"> Hugh of St. Victor </persName> and ‘<persName key="person_34854285" role="aut">
                           <!-- check identification? --> Odo canonicus </persName>’, also a group by <persName key="person_102305735" role="aut"> Caesarius of Arles </persName> (fol.213–21v) and another group found in Carolingian homiliaries including a homily by <persName key="person_79148266" role="aut"> Haymo of Auxerre </persName> (fol.187v–91v, 192v–5v)</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_d_35-item3">
                     <locus>(fol.228–95v)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14583">Sermons</title>
                     <note>Further sermons and short pieces, including extracts from <persName key="person_100184667" role="aut">Gregory</persName>, <title key="work_1876">Moralia in Job</title> and from sermons of <persName key="person_59875293" role="aut"> Bernard of Clairvaux </persName>, and sentences from the school of <persName key="person_77109407" role="aut"> Anselm of Laon </persName>.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_d_35-item4">
                     <locus>(fol.295v–9v)</locus>
                     <author key="person_282035032">Hildebert of Lavardin</author>
                     <title key="work_2055">Letters</title>
                     <note>Ep. VIII and XXIII.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_d_35-item5">
                     <locus>(fol.30va–31vb, 98vb–99vb, 224vb–227vb)</locus>
                     <author key="person_54538580">Geoffrey Babion</author>
                     <title key="work_1660">Sermons</title>
                     <note>Added by a hand different from the main scribe, in spaces originally left blank.</note>
                  </msItem>
